<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<!DOCTYPE task PUBLIC "-//OASIS//DTD DITA Task//EN" "task.dtd" []>
<task xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" id="editing-attributes" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="urn:oasis:names:tc:dita:xsd:task.xsd:1.1">
  <title>Editing Attributes</title>
<?serna-redline-start 0 to be refactored
this must be a concept, not task
subtopics must be created describing attribute operations?>  <taskbody>
    <context>
      <p>When you point the cursor over an element in the <xref href="content-map.xml">ContentMap</xref>, you can see a hint with its attributes.</p>
      <image href="attribute-hint.png" align="center" placement="break"/>
      <p>You can edit attributes of an element:<ul>
          <li>
            <p>Add a new attribute.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>Delete an attribute.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>Change the value of an attribute.</p>
          </li>
        </ul></p>
      <p>To edit attributes of an element, do the following:</p>
    </context>
    <steps>
      <step>
        <cmd>Place the cursor on the element.</cmd>
        <info>
          <p>Place the cursor in the element in the <xref href="editing-window.xml">Editing Window</xref> or click the element in the <xref href="content-map.xml">ContentMap</xref>.</p>
        </info>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Call up the <keyword>Element Attributes Dialog</keyword>.</cmd>
        <info>
          <p>To call up the <keyword>Element Attributes Dialog</keyword> (or move the focus to the docked <keyword>Element Attributes Dialog</keyword>), do one of the following:</p>
        </info>
        <choices>
          <choice>
            <p>Press <uicontrol>Alt-Enter</uicontrol>.</p>
          </choice>
          <choice>
            <p>Choose <menucascade>
                <uicontrol>Element</uicontrol>
                <uicontrol>Element Attributes</uicontrol>
              </menucascade>.</p>
          </choice>
          <choice>
            <p>Click the <uicontrol>Element Attributes</uicontrol> button <image href="element-attributes-button.png" align="center" placement="inline"/> on the toolbar.</p>
          </choice>
          <choice>
            <p>Right-click and select <uicontrol>Element Attributes</uicontrol> from the context menu.</p>
          </choice>
        </choices>
        <stepresult>
          <p>The <keyword>Element Attributes Dialog</keyword> will appear.</p>
          <fig>
            <title>Element Attributes Dialog</title>
            <image href="attributes-dialog.png" align="center" placement="break"/>
          </fig>
          <note id="docking">
            <p>The <keyword>Element Attributes Dialog</keyword> is a  <q>liquid dialog</q>: it can have a different, docked appearance. For  more information about liquid dialogs, see <xref href="docking.xml"/>.</p>
          </note>
        </stepresult>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>In the <keyword>Element Attributes Dialog</keyword>, edit attributes of the element:</cmd>
        <substeps>
          <substep>
            <cmd>Add an attribute.</cmd>
            <info>
              <p>To add an attribute, do the following:<ol>
                  <li>
                    <p>Click the <b>
                        <uicontrol>Add Attribute</uicontrol>
                      </b> button <image href="add-attribute-button.png" align="center" placement="inline"/>.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <p> In the <uicontrol>Name</uicontrol> combo-box, select or type the attribute&apos;s name.</p>
                    <note>
                      <p>A list of allowed attributes is provided if <xref href="validation-modes.xml">validation is on</xref>.</p>
                    </note>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <p>In the <uicontrol>Value</uicontrol> combo-box, select or  type the attribute&apos;s value.</p>
                    <note>
                      <p>To insert a relative file name as the attribute&apos;s value, browse for the file using the <uicontrol>Browse</uicontrol> button <image href="browse-button.png" align="center" placement="inline"/>.</p>
                    </note>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <p>Press <uicontrol>Enter</uicontrol>.</p>
                  </li>
                </ol></p>
            </info>
          </substep>
          <substep>
            <cmd>Change an attribute&apos;s value.</cmd>
            <info>
              <p>To change the value of an attribute, do the following:<ol>
                  <li>
                    <p>In the <uicontrol>Value</uicontrol> combo-box, select or type the new value of the attribute.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <p>Press <uicontrol>Enter</uicontrol>.</p>
                  </li>
                </ol></p>
              <note>
                <p>To restore the default value of an attribute, click the attribute and click the <uicontrol>Set Default Value</uicontrol> button <image href="set-default-attribute-value-button.png" align="center"/>.</p>
              </note>
            </info>
          </substep>
          <substep>
            <cmd>Delete an attribute</cmd>
            <info>
              <p>To delete an attribute, click the attribute and click the <uicontrol>Delete Attribute</uicontrol> button <image href="delete-attribute-button.png" align="center"/>.</p>
            </info>
          </substep>
        </substeps>
        <info>
          <note>
            <p>The meanings of icons are as follows:<ul>
                <li>
                  <image href="default_attribute.png" placement="inline"/>
                  <p>This attribute has a default value defined in Schema.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <image href="required_attribute.png" placement="inline"/>
                  <p>This is a required attribute.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <image href="fixed_attribute.png" placement="inline"/>
                  <p>Attribute has a fixed value.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <image href="ID_attribute_type.png" placement="inline"/>
                  <p>Attribute has ID type.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <image href="IDREF_attribute_type.png" placement="inline"/>
                  <p>Attribute has IDREF type.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <image href="custom_attribute_type.png" placement="inline"/>
                  <p>Attribute has a custom type (Schema data-type).</p>
                </li>
              </ul></p>
          </note>
        </info>
        <info>
          <note>
            <p>You can <xref href="using-element-help.xml">call up help</xref>  for an attribute.</p>
          </note>
        </info>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Close the dialog.</cmd>
        <info>
          <p>To close the <keyword>Element Attributes Dialog</keyword>, click the <uicontrol>Close</uicontrol> button.</p>
        </info>
      </step>
    </steps>
    <example>
      <title>Example. Changing an attribute.</title>
      <p>Let&apos;s change the <codeph>role</codeph> attribute of the <codeph>emphasis</codeph> element:<ol>
          <li>
            <p>Click the &quot;<codeph>Apple</codeph>&quot; <codeph>emphasis</codeph> element.</p>
            <image href="cursor-in-italic.png" align="center" placement="break"/>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>Press <uicontrol>Alt-Enter</uicontrol> to call up the <keyword>Element Attributes Dialog</keyword>.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>In the <keyword>Element Attributes Dialog</keyword>, click  the <b>
                <uicontrol>Add Attribute</uicontrol>
              </b> button <image href="add-attribute-button.png" align="center" placement="inline"/> and select the  <codeph>role</codeph> attribute.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>Type the <codeph>underline</codeph>  value and press <uicontrol>Enter</uicontrol>.</p>
            <image href="emphasis-role.png" align="center" placement="break"/>
            <p>The <codeph>emphasis</codeph> is now underlined.</p>
            <image href="underline.png" align="center" placement="break"/>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>Type the <codeph>bold</codeph> value of the <codeph>role</codeph> attribute and press <uicontrol>Enter</uicontrol>.</p>
            <p>The <codeph>emphasis</codeph> is now bold.</p>
            <image href="bold-emphasis.png" align="center" placement="break"/>
          </li>
        </ol></p>
    </example>
  </taskbody>
<?serna-redline-end?></task>
